Blocks.Text: Exploring Model Dynamics for Accumulative Poisoning Discovery
Figure 1. Left: Accumulative poisoning attack compared with conventional poisoning attack. Right: Comparison of the
distributions using static information (e.g., outputs mainly on current model) with discrepancy information.
As the accumulative poisoning attack utilize the sequential order property of real-time data
streaming for sneaky poisoning generation, we raise the following question:
Can we also exploit the information of model dynamics to gain some useful clues to
identify the imperceptible accumulative poisoning attacks?
